  "title": "HR Generalist",
  "description": "<p>HR Generalist - Engineering Design and Technical Consultancy MNC</p><p>Salary: $6000 max</p><p>5 days work week</p><p>Location: Tuas</p><p><br /></p><p>Job Scope:</p><p><strong>Employee Life Cycle Management</strong></p><p>·  Manages ELC activities in close collaboration with HR Partner for the designated area of responsibility</p><p>·  Manages onboarding and offboarding events in close liaison with recruiting team, hiring managers and ensuring correct work permits</p><p>·  Collect feedback along the life cycle support from the organization for continuous improvements.</p><p>·  Promote Self Service to the local organization</p><p><strong>HR Operational Excellence</strong></p><p>·  Understand and act according to Group/local policies & guidelines as well as relevant local statutory or regulatory requirements, support local policies review and communication when needed</p><p>·  Ensure SOP is well documented, updated and stored in the share folder including all HR processes from onboarding to offboarding, regional payroll, time management etc.</p><p>·  Ensuring that systems and databases have up-to-date employee and organizational information with high data quality and accuracy, and providing reports where required; Monitors HR data quality and integrity (GDPR) on regular basis and ensure appropriate governance</p><p>·  Establish secure and sufficient documentation management for internal and external audit</p><p>·  Identifies and recommends enhancements and simplification of existing processes/tools based on feedback and experience with internal customers.</p><p>·  Ensures that local & regional payroll is proceeded based on defined SOP with accurate information and sufficient supporting documentation.</p><p>Manages interface to external vendor from an operational point of view resulting in correct settlement for our employees.</p>",
